## Conventions

1. **Domain**: No `dart:io`, no `dart:ffi`, no platform-specific imports. Pure Dart types and exceptions.
2. **Value objects**: Define all domain value objects using **Dart extension types**. IDs and handles: `extension type X(int value)`. Multi-field values: `extension type X(RecordType _)` with explicit getters. See [docs/domain-model.md](../../docs/domain-model.md).
3. **Application**: Contains the main `ScreenCaptureKit` facade and use-case entry points. Calls into domain and into infrastructure via ports (or direct impl if no port yet).
4. **Aggregate**: Only `ShareableContent` is the aggregate root for the “shareable content” boundary; entities are referenced via the root. See docs/domain-model.md.
5. **Infrastructure**: All FFI and `if (dart.library.io)` platform code lives here. Depends only on domain (and ports if defined).
6. **Presentation**: Public-facing config types and handles (the surface "presented" to the consumer); re-exports from application/domain as needed. No business logic. Not a UI layer.
7. **Imports**: Inner layers must not import outer layers. Use dependency inversion (interfaces in application/domain, implementations in infrastructure) when application needs to call infrastructure.

## Refactoring Checklist

When moving code toward this architecture:

- [ ] Identify each file’s layer (domain / application / infrastructure / presentation).
- [ ] Move files into the target folders above; fix imports so they respect the dependency rule.
- [ ] Ensure domain has zero dependencies on other layers.
- [ ] Introduce ports (abstract interfaces) in application if infrastructure is invoked from application. Expose an abstract application port (e.g. `ScreenCaptureKitPort`) and have the facade implement it so that apps and CLI tools can inject mocks in tests.
- [ ] Keep the public barrel (`screen_capture_kit.dart`) exporting only the intended API surface.
- [ ] Document filter lifecycle in API docs and README: every `ContentFilterHandle` must be released with `releaseFilter(handle)`; recommend `try/finally`.
- [ ] Implement value objects as **extension types** per docs/domain-model.md (IDs on `int`, multi-field on records with getters). Migrate existing value types (e.g. Display, Window dimensions; CapturedFrame, CapturedImage, CapturedAudio; ContentFilterHandle) to extension types and have entities use them (e.g. Display uses DisplayId and FrameSize).

## Design review

The layering is appropriate for this package; recommend exposing an application port for DI and documenting filter lifecycle clearly.
